A Treasure Room
You can see a treasure chest, a jar of sustenance and a table (on which there is a selket, a senet board and a sistrum).
You can go south or east.
When archeologist Howard Carter first peered into King Tut's tomb in 1922, he was asked, "Can you see anything?" and he famously replied, "Yes, wonderful things!" That's how you feel right now. If you carried the treasures out of here, you would be rich beyond your wildest imagination.

> open sesame

> open sesame
The hidden door opens to your magic spell. You ask yourself if you have the courage to enter.
> w

> w
A Burial Chamber
You can see a sarcophagus, a canopic jar 1, a canopic jar 2, a canopic jar 3 and a canopic jar 4.
You can go east, south or in.
The burial chamber of King Haputet. Hieroglyphs are engraved on the wall.
Booby trap! A stone block poised over the door falls on your head. At least there was only one.
The block hurts you!

> translate hieroglyphs

> translate hieroglyphs
The hieroglyphs say, "Lighten the heavy, and enliven the dead. Say this word: appum"
> lock sarcophagus

> lock sarcophagus
You thread the Flail of Anubis through the latch holes, locking the sarcophagus shut.
> say appum

> say appum
In a sonorous voice, you shout, "Appum!"
Your hair stands on end.
